# Spec 002 — Home-value dataset enrichment

Status: Draft
Owner: <you>
Related: builds on 001-mvp (value-only choropleth)

## Overview

The MVP shades each ZIP by a single scalar median home value. This feature
enriches each ZIP with additional market signal — **year-over-year % change**, a
**5-year trend (CAGR)**, **median price per square foot ($/sqft)**, and a small
**price-history sparkline** — and exposes it two ways: a **metric switcher** that
re-shades the map (Value / YoY / $/sqft), and a **richer hover/tap popup** that
shows all metrics plus the sparkline.

## Context

- YoY, CAGR, and history are derived for free from the Zillow ZHVI ZIP CSV the
  build already downloads (it carries the full monthly history per ZIP; same
  month-to-month, already smoothed + seasonally adjusted).
- $/sqft is not in ZHVI at ZIP level. It comes from the **Redfin
  `zip_code_market_tracker`** dataset (`MEDIAN_PPSF` — median sold price per
  square foot, All Residential). Redfin is an **optional** second source: a large
  one-time download filtered to a small committed file; the app must work (with
  $/sqft greyed out) when it is absent.

## Requirements

- **R1 — Enriched per-ZIP record.** Each ZIP exposes `median_value` (required)
  plus optional `yoy_pct`, `cagr5_pct`, `ppsf`, and `history`. Missing optional
  metrics are omitted, never fatal (consistent with 001 R1).
- **R2 — ZHVI-derived metrics.** `yoy_pct` (latest vs ~12 months prior),
  `cagr5_pct` (annualized over ~5 years), and a downsampled `history` series are
  computed from the existing ZHVI monthly columns.
- **R3 — $/sqft from Redfin.** When the Redfin source is supplied, each matched
  ZIP gets `ppsf`; when it is not, `ppsf` is absent and the app degrades cleanly.
- **R4 — Metric switcher.** The user can switch the choropleth between Value, YoY,
  and $/sqft. Each metric has its own color ramp and legend; YoY uses a diverging
  scale centered on 0. ZIPs lacking the active metric render as "no data".
- **R5 — Richer popup.** Hovering/tapping a ZIP shows median value, YoY (with
  up/down emphasis), 5-year CAGR, $/sqft (or an "n/a" note), and a sparkline of
  the price history.
- **R6 — Key safety preserved.** No new client-exposed secrets; the frontend still
  only calls its own origin (001 R5 intact).

## Non-functional / Constraints

- Only free/aggregate data; committed as small preprocessed files. Redfin's raw
  file is large — it must be stream-filtered to Seattle ZIPs, not committed raw.
- Map re-shading on metric switch is a paint change only (no data refetch).
- $/sqft is sourced from sold transactions (`MEDIAN_PPSF`) and labeled "sold"
  in the popup.

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] `seattle_zhvi.json` records carry `yoy_pct`, `cagr5_pct`, and `history`;
      `ppsf` is present after a Redfin-enabled build and absent otherwise.
- [ ] Switching the active metric re-shades the map and swaps the legend; YoY
      shows declining ZIPs in a distinct hue from rising ones.
- [ ] A ZIP popup shows value, YoY, 5-year CAGR, $/sqft (or n/a), and a sparkline.
- [ ] ZIPs missing the active metric (e.g. no `ppsf`) render as "no data", not a
      crash or a misleading color.
- [ ] The browser Network tab shows no Mapbox token in any client request.
- [ ] `pytest` (backend) and `npm run test` (frontend) pass.

## Out of Scope (explicit)

- Market-activity metrics (homes sold, days on market, sale-to-list, inventory) —
  available from Redfin but not included here.
- Time-scrubbing the map (animating the history); the sparkline is static.
- Forecasting / optimization (future specs).

## Verification notes

Each criterion traces to a requirement: enriched record → R1/R2/R3; switcher +
diverging YoY → R4; popup + sparkline → R5; no-data handling → R1/R4; token
absence → R6. Verify by walking this list against a running build; the
implementing agent does not self-certify done.
